experiences:
Second level report to the CEO, Sergio Marchionne.
Reports about Sustainability issues to the Board of Directors. Located in Turin (Italy). 

Responsible at global level, Chrysler Group included for:
Processes, group-wide strategy for sustainability and the cultural change linked to the integration of social and environmental issues in ordinary business processes;
External communication in particular the Sustainability Report and the website; 
Definition of the Sustainability Plan and coordination of projects;
KPIs definition and monitoring process (500 KPIs monitored);
Relations with rating agencies and SRIs (Socially Responsible Investors);
Relations with NGOs and, for specific issues, with the European sector association.

Under her leadership, Fiat was admitted to the Dow Jones Sustainability Index World and Europe, the most prestigious sustainability equity indexes and  was awarded with the maximum score for the results in reducing carbon emissions (Carbon Performance Leadership Index). Moreover the shares held by Socially Responsible Investors reached the 9% of the free float of the company.

